Interface RDMDirectoryMsgCallback

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ConsumerCallback, ProviderCallback
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Consumer, Provider, QueueConsumer, WatchlistConsumer

    public interface RDMDirectoryMsgCallback
    The RDM directory message callback is used to communicate directory message events to the application.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      int rdmDirectoryMsgCallback(RDMDirectoryMsgEvent event)
      A callback function that the Reactor will use to communicate directory message events to the application.

    • Method Detail

      • rdmDirectoryMsgCallback

        int rdmDirectoryMsgCallback(RDMDirectoryMsgEvent event)
        A callback function that the Reactor will use to communicate directory message events to the application.
        Parameters:
        event - A ReactorMsgEvent containing event information. The ReactorMsgEvent is valid only during callback
        Returns:
        ReactorCallbackReturnCodes A callback return code that can trigger specific Reactor behavior based on the outcome of the callback function
        See Also:
        RDMDirectoryMsgEvent, ReactorCallbackReturnCodes
